The paper deals with the application of deep learning for automatic detection of atherosclerotic carotid plaques on panoramic images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.DL). The use of medical images also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.MS). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential application of the algorithm in routine dental practice, which could fall under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
